Abdomen:
Dorsally abdominal tergites VI–VIII pigmented and setose, VII and VIII densely covered with long setae; abdominal sternites II + III (ventrite I) 2X size of sternite IV, sternites IV–VII similar in size and form, sternite VIII (ventrite VI) triangular, bifid apically in females, trilobate in males (
Fig. 6A, B
